<br>
I got a pick-up group together for a South Ro dungeon adventure.  This group consisted of Chimerian (an enchantress), Nojobo (warrior), Kittii (beastlord), myself (aanladarie, a cleric), Kelvarien (paladin), and Kevarien's real life girlfriend, Kerane (druid).  <br>
<br>
There was bickering and tension almost from the start.  Nobody realized the add situation with the little goblin punks.  A couple died.  We're all 20s, so no big deal.  Kevarien started to complain that the casters were doing too much fighting.  The only caster fighting at all was his girlfriend who was sitting right beside him.<br>
<br>
A few more minutes into it, I died.  Again, no big deal.  I didn't even rez myself - didn't want to lose time waiting for mana and for rez effects to wear off.<br>
<br>
Kevarien complains more.  I am keeping the rest of the group from telling him where to stick it in tells.<br>
<br>
Finally we are reaching the point where it's very clear that we aren't going to complete the mission.  One more thing that just isn't a big deal - we fail a mission.  Then the bickering gets a little heavier.  Nojobo and Kevarien start calling the other's skills into question.  Kevarien was pulling and we were rarely without at least two adds.<br>
<br>
Kevarien starts name-calling.  Kevarien, who was master-looting at my request, then states that the rest of us are just going to have to go without loot or money from our little adventure.  I end the adventure.  One more case of no big deal.  The loot in these dungeons at this level is really minimal, and this won't be my last crawl.<br>
<br>
More name-calling from Kevarien.  I really felt badly for his girlfriend.  She was silent through everything.  I apologized sincerely to the entire group other than Kevarien, as he was the source of the trouble.<br>
<br>
Just wanted to relate my cautionary tale. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luminargu>LuminarGU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:green;'>Tavern Patron</span></span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(10/1/03 1:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3573.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.twcny.rr.com/jeffd/musicgirl2large.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kevarien</span><hr size=1> isnt there a &quot;must be of level 50 or higher to post here&quot; on the sign outside? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32524" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.twcny.rr.com/jeffd/sig713.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dixxycupp>Dixxy Cupp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(10/1/03 3:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3573.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kevarien</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> isnt there a &quot;must be of level 50 or higher to post here&quot; on the sign outside?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Hmm, I don't remember seeing that sign... And, sadly, I<br>
